Prism Adept Serai was a Spirebound Conclave technical specialist from the Prism Thesis faction, the faction that pursued structure through crystal harmonics and resonance geometry. The Prism Thesis held that the underlying structure of magical phenomena was geometrically expressible — that the relationships between spell schools, the interference and amplification effects that the Chromatic Circle's Confluence Texts documented empirically, had a geometric foundation that could be mapped precisely in crystal harmonic diagrams. Serai's specific contribution was the conduit diagrams: a unified notation system that represented both the crystal theory (which spell schools resonated at which harmonic intervals) and the operational architecture (how those resonances could be activated through practitioner channeling). The diagrams were the Prism Thesis faction's closest approach to the Axiomatic Schools' replication standard — a notation precise enough that a practitioner working from the diagrams could reproduce the documented effects without requiring apprentice-chain transmission. Serai's conduit diagrams survived the Spirebound Conclave's catastrophe in several partial copies, which entered circulation through the Violet Compact's institutional reorganization period. Current scholarship treats the diagrams as a live technical resource: the notation system is still used by crystal-resonance practitioners to document new interaction effects, and the diagrams' organizational structure has influenced how several practitioner traditions document multi-school interaction phenomena. Serai's identity and biography are incompletely documented; the name appears in Conclave records as a faculty designation rather than a personal name, and whether Prism Adept was a rank title or an individual descriptor is an open historiographical question.

